Implement vector initialisation

To avoid having to first create a vector and push items to it in manual
step let the compiler handle initialisation:

    (let v (vector (1 2 3 4)))

Much better than this:

    (let v (vector))
    (Std.Vector.push v 1)
    (Std.Vector.push v 2)
    (Std.Vector.push v 3)
    (Std.Vector.push v 4)

More maintainable, less error prone. What's not to like?
